{
  "description": "A wide-angle shot capturing a panoramic view of San Francisco Bay. The iconic Golden Gate Bridge dominates the right side of the frame, its reddish-orange towers contrasting against the blue sky and water. Several smaller bridges span the bay in the middle ground, connecting to the city skyline on the left. The San Francisco skyline includes recognizable high-rise buildings and structures. The bay itself is a dark, choppy blue, with a small red buoy visible in the foreground. The sky is filled with fluffy white and grey clouds, indicating a partly cloudy day. There's evidence of maritime traffic with several boats and ships visible on the water.",
